  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add the<strong> chicken breast portions </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-18 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684152454709-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684152454709-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684152454709-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684152454709-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684152454709-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan or pot (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> and <strong>diced carrot</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Remove 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> butter</strong> from the fridge to warm up for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684152457729-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684152457729-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684152457729-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684152457729-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684152457729-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is softening, finely dice the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on)</p><p>Slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 600ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.2L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696855960349-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1696855960349-x400.jpg",
