          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-15 min or until the potatoes are just fork tender</p><p>Meanwhile, strip the<strong> thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and add them to the pan, discard the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the thyme sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684152467150-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684152467150-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684152467150-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684152467150-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684152467150-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the soup is cooking, slice the<strong> ciabattas </strong>in half</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> remaining chopped garlic </strong>with the <strong>warmed butter</strong>, then spread it over the<strong> ciabatta halves</strong> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Once the soup is almost done, put the tray in the oven for 5-7 min or until crusty – this is your<strong> garlic bread</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684152470112-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684152470112-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684152470112-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684152470112-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684152470112-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the<strong> cooked chicken</strong> from the oven and transfer to a clean board, then shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Stir the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> into the soup with the<strong> soft cheese</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong>, then lightly mash the soup to break up a few potatoes and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy pulled chicken soup</strong></p><p>Tip: If your soup is too thick, add a small splash of water!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684152472501-x200.jpg",
